info.title: Apigee Nucleus API
info.description: Maps components of Apigee Customer Environments to an API

get.description: A collection of Apigee Organizations. An organization is the base container for all objects in an API provider's account on Apigee Edge.

parameters.name: Authorization
parameters.description: Header Param Description. Obtain a valid access token here. https://apigeesc.atlassian.net/wiki/display/NUCLEUS/API+Security

parameters.name: limit
parameters.description: Number of items to be returned. Default 100 and Max 100.

parameters.name: where
parameters.description: Filter items by more specific criteria. Check Sequelize.js Querying syntax along with describe parameter in Base64 encoding. Return all orgs containing the word 'net' in it would be represented as '{"org_name": {"$like":"%net%"}}' and in base64 as %7B%22org_name%22%3A%20%7B%22%24like%22%3A%22%25net%25%22%7D%7D.

parameters.name: stacktrace
parameters.description: Useful for development purposes. Returns more information about the error.

parameters.name: attributes
parameters.description: Include only attributes from this list. See describe parameter to retrieve a list of valid attributes. e.g. ["org_name","account_id","paid"]

parameters.name: include
parameters.description: Include subresources. e.g. [{"name": "APIS"}]

parameters.name: offset
parameters.description: Used for paginating records of a collection.
